<div id="banner">
	<h1>Rights Fight</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>I need a lawyer willing to argue that not-for-profit file sharing is fair use. I&#8217;ve got a plan.</p>

<p><a href="http://www.napster.com/">Napster: Work in Progress</a> &#8212; that&#8217;s new. They&#8217;re also selling merchandise.</p>

<p><a href="http://www.mp3isnotacrime.org/">MP3 Is Not a Crime</a> is a weblog covering the attacks on our rights.</p>

<p>Dave Winer says <a href="http://scriptingnews.userland.com/backissues/2002/09/24#When:8:35:25AM">he&#8217;s not afraid to defend our rights</a>. <em>Yes! Who else?</em></p>

<p>&lt;coderman> I will now refer to file sharing networks as &#8220;fair use networks&#8221;<br />
&lt;coderman> like my limewire fair use network client..  or the kazaa fair use network..</p>

<p class="posted">posted September 24, 2002 11:03 AM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_politics">Politics</a>)  <a href="000614" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

